.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the subject is to support students' successful coping at the university, the growth of self-awareness and their planning of their study plan  so that the student feels part of the university. The course offers relevant information, different cooperational and creative activities to support a sense of belonging and understanding about chosen curriculum.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course the student - has obtained an overview of the different areas of curriculum and its possible directions of specialization, and draws up his/her study plan for the entire study periood - knows where to find study information and support  - has analysed his/her study habbits and learning techniques  - has participated in group activies  - knows how to take care his/her mentaal, physical and emotional health
